nnual general meeting on may th either smurfit kappa has meanwhile appointed former carlsberg chief executive jorgen buhl rasmussen to the board with immediate effect mr mcgann’s decision to step down from smurfit kappa’s board comes as he seeks to overhaul aryzta whose shares have slumped by  per cent over the past two years amid a series of profit warnings and weak earnings statements last month the group’s chief executive owen killian chief financial officer patrick mceniff and head of the americas division john yamin each tendered their resignation  just weeks after it issued the latest profits alert the company now has a market value of € billion aryzta also signalled last month that it would sell its  per cent stake in french frozen foods company picard which it acquired two years ago for € million the acquisition was badly received at the time by analysts aryzta also faces having to refinance € million of debt within the next year       topics denis lucey gary mcgann john yamin liam o mahony owen killan patrick mceniff thomas brodin aryzta smurfit kappa read more crh back on acquisitions trail after  earnings jump manufacturing activity continues to improve but at slower rate takata plea and compensation deal clear path to potential sale ardagh group increases bond sale value to bn goldman sachs and davy among ardagh ipo underwriters ardagh launches bn bond sale to cut costs ahead of ipo wild geese dublin designer making his mark in denmark failed kraft plan puts the focus back on unilever demand for ukmanufactured goods rises to twoyear high french socialists unfazed by pending opel takeover  subscribe   more from the irish times technology decision on apple’s €m data centre in athenry postponed work staff at aidan o’brien stables work up to hour days labour court told golf out of bounds us pga set for new lease of life as year’s second major retail  services profit growth slows at zara parent sponsored wild islands of the wild atlantic way the dublin story 